<!DOCTYPE HTML>
<html>
	<head>
		<!-- Prevents against cross-site scripting attacks that use UTF-7 -->
		<meta charset='utf-8'>
		
		<!--  Set width to pixel width of screen, so display isn't zoomed out
		      by default.  Mainly for mobile, but doesn't hurt on desktop. -->
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
		
		<!-- Desktop-specific CSS -->
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="http://code.jquery.com/ui/1.10.2/themes/smoothness/jquery-ui.css" />
		
		<!--  Custom CSS -->
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="common.css" />
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="berkeley.css" />
		
		<!--  Use Google CDN when possible, since it is very common, and 
		      will probably already have downloaded to user's device.  
		      Scripts are generally cached by the device once downloaded,
		      with each CDN seen as unique, even if the script is the same.  -->
		<script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.9.1/jquery.min.js"> </script>
		
		<!-- Desktop-specific JS-->
		<!-- jQueryUI not available through Google CDN -->
		<!--  Used for toggle checkboxes -->
		<script src="http://code.jquery.com/ui/1.10.2/jquery-ui.js"></script>
		
		<!--  Heat map graphic uses the d3 library --> 
		<script src="http://d3js.org/d3.v3.min.js"> </script>
		<script src="heatmap.js"> </script>

		<title> Smart Room </title>
	</head>

	<body>	
 	
 	<!-- Content -->

	<div>
		<!-- Toggle radio group from jQueryUI -->
		<div id="radio-group" class="radio-group">
			<input type="radio" id="radio1" name="radio" checked="checked" onclick="postMarkers()"/><label for="radio1">View Heat Map</label>
			<input type="radio" id="radio2" name="radio" onclick="clearHeatMap()"/><label for="radio2">Move Markers</label>
		</div>
		
		<div id="room-map"> 
		
		</div>
	</div>
	
	 <div> 
	 	 <p> This demo shows a room with five light sources and three sensors. </p>
	 	 <p> The Ptolemy web server calculates the light received at each sensor <br>
	 	     and a heat map of the illumination at each point in the room. </p>
	 	 <p> The lights and sensors may be moved in the "Move Markers" tab. <br>
	 	     Please wait while the heat map loads... </p>
 	
 	</div>
	
	<!-- Footer --> 
	<footer data-role="footer"> 
		<ul> 
			<li> </li>
		</ul>
	</footer>
	
	</body>
</html>
